The '''John Richardson Homestead''' is a historic house on Hancock Road in [[Dublin, New Hampshire]].  The 2-1/2 story wood frame house was built c. 1798 John Richardson, whose brother Abijah [[Abijah Richardson, Sr. Homestead|built his house]] further down the road on the same lot.  The house is basically Federal in massing, five bays wide and two deep, but it was updated later with Greek Revival features, including corner pilasters and a center entry framed by sidelight windows.<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=83004072}}|title=NRHP nomination for John Richardson Homestead|publisher=National Park Service|accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

The house was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1983.<ref name="nris"/>

